alert.note: Alert for Coastal Levy; Inland Levy (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay
info.description: ...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northern Citrus, northwestern Sumter and Levy Counties through 545 PM EDT... At 445 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along a line extending from near Chiefland to near Rainbow Lakes Estates to Inverness Highlands South. Movement was northeast at 40 mph. HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Williston, Chiefland, Bronson, Beverly Hills, Homosassa Springs, Williston Highlands, East Bronson, Crystal River Airport, Manattee Road, Black Diamond, Andrews, Williston Municipal Airport, Fowlers Bluff, Inverness Highlands North, Homosassa, Hernando, Inglis, Otter Creek, Arbor Lakes, and Lecanto. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for northern, central and west central Florida.
